==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Upholsterer
<hw>Up*hol"ster*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A substitution
for older <ets>upholder</ets>, in OE., broker, tradesman, and formerly
also written <asp>upholster</asp>, <asp>upholdster</asp>. See
<er>Upholder</er>, and <er>-ster</er>.]</ety> <def>One who provides
hangings, coverings, cushions, curtains, and the like; one who
upholsters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Upholsterer bee</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Poppy bee</cref>, under <er>Poppy</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upholstery</ent>⟦br⟧
